  "prompt": "Why is Franz Ferdinand famous?",
  "response": "Franz Ferdinand is most famous for his assassination, which was a significant event that led to the outbreak of World War I. Archduke Franz Ferdinand was the heir presumptive to the Austro-Hungarian throne. On June 28, 1914, he and his wife, Sophie, were killed in Sarajevo by Gavrilo Princip, a Bosnian Serb nationalist. This assassination triggered a series of diplomatic crises and alliances that eventually escalated into the global conflict known as World War I.",
